<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall brown. Pronotal disc of variable color, from having paired pink spots to entirely pink (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6A, C, F</figureCitation>
), pronotal expansions dark brown, often brighter at anterior corners. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6A, C</figureCitation>
) dark brown with a pale-yellow longitudinal stripe as long as about 4/5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
elytron length. Legs dark brown, except for trochanters, which are light brown. Sternum VIII with lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Figure 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys bella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
